"content": "<style>\nh1.thlex-title { font-size: 1.3em; margin: 0 0 0.4em; }\n.thlex-key { color: #888; font-size: 0.85em; font-weight: normal; margin-right: 0.4em; }\nnav.thlex-index { margin: 0.5em 0 0.75em; }\nnav.thlex-index ul { margin: 0; padding-left: 1.2em; }\nnav.thlex-index li { margin: 0.15em 0; font-size: 0.95em; }\n.thlex-section { margin: 0.6em 0; }\nh2.thlex-heading { font-size: 1em; margin: 0.5em 0 0.2em; }\nh3.thlex-subheading { font-size: 0.95em; font-weight: normal; font-style: italic; margin: 0.2em 0; }\n.thlex-language-sets { margin: 0.3em 0 0.3em 1em; }\n.thlex-language-set { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 0.75em; border-left: 3px solid #e0e0e0; }\n.thlex-language { font-size: 0.8em; color: #888; margin-right: 0.4em; }\n.thlex-lemma { font-weight: bold; font-family: serif; }\n.thlex-translit { color: #555; font-style: italic; font-size: 0.9em; margin-left: 0.3em; }\n.thlex-refs { font-size: 0.85em; color: #444; margin-top: 0.15em; }\n.thlex-paragraphs p { margin: 0.35em 0; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.5; }\n.thlex-image { margin: 0.5em 0; display: block; }\n.thlex-image img { max-width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; }\nfigcaption.thlex-caption { font-size: 0.85em; color: #555; font-style: italic; margin-top: 0.2em; }\n.thlex-abbr { border-bottom: 1px dotted #888; cursor: help; }\n.thlex-xref { color: #1a5fb4; }\nspan[data-bnType=\"bibleReference\"] { color: #1a5fb4; }\ntable.thlex-table { border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 0.9em; margin: 0.5em 0; }\ntable.thlex-table td { padding: 0.2em 0.6em; vertical-align: top; border: 1px solid #ddd; }\ntable.thlex-table tr:first-child td { font-weight: bold; background: #f5f5f5; }\nul.thlex-index-list { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.6; }\nul.thlex-index-list ul { margin: 0.1em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; }\n.thlex-index-key { font-weight: bold; font-style: italic; }\n</style><h1 class=\"thlex-title\" id=\"REALIA:3.10\"><span class=\"thlex-key\">3.10</span> 標題：水池（pool）</h1><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">經文出處</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-sets\">\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">來： בְּרֵכָה</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： brekah)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam2:13\">2SA 2:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam2:13\">2SA 2:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam2:13\">2SA 2:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam4:12\">2SA 4:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs22:38\">1KI 22:38</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs18:17\">2KI 18:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs20:20\">2KI 20:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh2:14\">NEH 2:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh3:15\">NEH 3:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh3:16\">NEH 3:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl2:6\">ECC 2:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song7:5\">SNG 7:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa7:3\">ISA 7:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa22:9\">ISA 22:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa22:11\">ISA 22:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa36:2\">ISA 36:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Nah2:9\">NAM 2:9</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">來： מִקְוֶה, מִקְוָה</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： miqveh, miqvah)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod7:19\">EXO 7:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa22:11\">ISA 22:11</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">希： κολυμβήθρα</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： kolumbēthra)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John5:2\">JHN 5:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John5:4\">JHN 5:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John5:7\">JHN 5:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John9:7\">JHN 9:7</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">希： κρήνη</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： krēnē)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Sir48:17\">SIR 48:17</a></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">描述和用途</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>\n            <figure class=\"thlex-image\"><img class=\"thlex-img\" src=\"images/WEB-0418_pool.jpg\" alt=\"下所羅門池\"><figcaption class=\"thlex-caption\">下所羅門池 (© Liadmalone, CC BY-SA 3.0, via Wikimedia Commons)</figcaption></figure>水池是一個相對較大、露天的蓄水構築物。</p>\n<hr/>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">翻譯</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>\n            <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod7:19\">EXO 7:19</a> ：在這節經文中，希伯來文<em>miqveh</em> 可能是指一種特殊的蓄水池，或者更有可能是一個通用詞語，重複前面的短語「埃及的水」。</p>\n<p>\n            <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa22:11\">ISA 22:11</a> ：在耶路撒冷的兩道城牆之間建造的水池可能有兩種用途：在圍城期間儲水，以及作護城河或灌滿水的壕溝來阻擋攻擊者。大多數譯本都把這裡的希伯來文<em>miqvah</em> 譯為“reservoir”（「水庫」；<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Good News Translation (1992)\">GNT</abbr> 、<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"New International Version (1984)\">NIV</abbr> ）。</p>\n<p>\n            <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Nah2:9\">NAM 2:9</a> （《和》2:8）：這節經文的希伯來文本有一個問題，許多譯本都是根據一個修訂過的文本進行翻譯的。水庫中的水往外流，比喻尼尼微人從城裡往外逃。因此，這節經文的前半部分可譯為：「尼尼微如同一個水池，裡面的水正在流失」（<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"New International Version (1984)\">NIV</abbr> 直譯），或「如水從裂開的大壩流出，居民也從尼尼微逃跑」（<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Good News Translation (1992)\">GNT</abbr> 直譯）。</p>\n<p>在<a href=\"https://ref.ly/John5:2\">JHN 5:2</a> ，希臘文<em>kolumbēthra</em> 指的是一個周圍有五個廊子的水池，水池四面各有一個廊子，還有一個横跨水池的中間。<a href=\"https://ref.ly/John9:7\">JHN 9:7</a> 出現了同一個希臘文，但該處提到的水池要小得多，也簡樸得多。這個水池已在耶路撒冷發掘出來。</p>\n</div>\n</div>",
